# Yumea Design System Rules

## 🎨 Color Scheme

- **Primary**: Black & White only
- **Background**: White with paper texture
- **Text**: Black (#000000) for headings, Gray (#374151) for body text
- **Accent**: Gold (#D4AF37) for brand highlights only
- **Borders**: Gray (#E5E7EB) for subtle boundaries

## 🚫 Avoid These UI Patterns

- **NO Card UI**: Remove all card backgrounds, shadows, and rounded corners
- **NO Colorful backgrounds**: No gradients, colored backgrounds, or vibrant colors
- **NO Colorful buttons**: Use only black/white with borders or shadows
- **NO Colorful badges**: Use border-only styling with gray text

## ✅ Preferred UI Patterns

- **Boundary-only design**: Use only bottom borders (`border-b-2 border-gray-200`) for sections
- **Clean layouts**: Minimal visual noise, focus on typography and spacing
- **Black outlines**: Use `border-2 border-black` for icons and important elements
- **Subtle shadows**: Use `shadow-lg` sparingly for depth

## 🎯 Brand Elements

- **Logo**: "유메아" in black, bold typography
- **Tagline**: "꿈을 꾸는 곳" in Dancing Script font, gold color (#D4AF37)
- **Typography**: Use Dancing Script for brand highlights only

## 📱 Responsive Design

- **Desktop**: 2-column layouts where appropriate
- **Mobile**: Single column, full-width layouts
- **Spacing**: Generous padding and margins for breathing room

## 🎨 Background Textures

- **Paper texture**: Use SVG data URLs with subtle opacity (20%)
- **Consistent**: Same paper texture across all pages
- **White base**: Always use white background with texture overlay

## 🔧 Technical Implementation

- **Tailwind CSS**: Use utility classes for all styling
- **No custom CSS**: Avoid custom stylesheets, use Tailwind utilities
- **Consistent spacing**: Use standard Tailwind spacing scale
- **Accessibility**: Maintain proper contrast ratios with black/white scheme

## 📋 Component Guidelines

- **Buttons**: Black border, white background, hover effects with color inversion
- **Navigation**: Simple text links with hover states
- **Sections**: Bottom borders only, no card styling
- **Icons**: Black fill, consistent sizing
- **Badges**: Border-only styling, no background colors

## 🎨 Visual Hierarchy

- **Headings**: Bold black text, clear size differentiation
- **Body text**: Gray for readability
- **Accents**: Gold only for brand elements
- **Spacing**: Generous whitespace for clean appearance

## 🚀 Performance

- **Optimize images**: Use appropriate formats and sizes
- **Minimal assets**: Keep design simple and lightweight
- **Fast loading**: Prioritize performance over visual complexity

Remember: This is a premium, minimalist brand. Every design decision should reinforce the black & white aesthetic while using gold sparingly for brand moments.
